  5. Evaluation (1–1.5 pages)

  This is where you show critical thinking:

  Metrics used and why:
  - P@10 — user-centric, most practical (cite Manning §8.3)
  - NDCG@10 — position-sensitive, handles graded relevance (cite Manning §8.4)
  - MRR — ideal for known-item queries like "Jabberwocky" (cite Manning §8.4)

  Relevance judgement process:
  - Pooling method — top 20 from each model, ~182 unique documents judged
  - Graded relevance: 2 = highly relevant, 1 = partially relevant, 0 = not relevant

